Class GBinary

java.lang.Object
  |

All Implemented Interfaces:
Cloneable, org.hs.util.Copy, GExpression, GStatement, at.dms.compiler.PhylumListener, Serializable
public class GBinary
extends GConstruct
implements GExpression, GStatement

GBinary represents an assortment of binary (i.e., two-sided) expressions which includes:

=
+, -, *, /
+=, -=, *=, /=
<<, >>, >>>
<<=, <<=, >>>=
&, |, ^
&=, |=, ^=

Assignment is indicated with the boolean compoundAssignment field. The static methods add(GExpression, GExpresion), subtract(...), multiply(...), etc. serve to enhance the readability of non-interactive code generation.
